Privacy Policy

Effective: March 2026

Overview

This Privacy Policy explains how NeuroVault handles your information. We design for privacy first, storing data on your device by default and minimizing external data transfer.

Information We Collect

Notes & Content: Text, tags, and metadata you create are stored locally on your device.

Device Data: Basic device information may be used to optimize app performance (e.g., theme, locale).

Optional Features: If you enable features like backups or notifications, we may store related preferences or schedule reminders on your device.

How We Use Information

We use your information to provide core functionality (create, search, and organize notes), personalize your experience (appearance and language), and maintain reliability (local backups, reminders).

Data Storage and Security

Your notes are stored on your device by default. If you export or back up your data, ensure you store it securely. We recommend using device-level protections such as screen locks and platform encryption.

Sharing and Third Parties

We do not sell your data. The app may integrate platform services (e.g., notifications, storage access) to operate features you enable. Any sharing you perform (export, share) is at your discretion.

Your Choices and Controls

You can manage your preferences in Settings, including language, appearance, and backups. You may export or delete your notes at any

time.

Children's Privacy

The app is not directed to children under the age required by local law to consent to data processing without parental involvement. If you believe a child has provided information, please remove it or contact support.
Changes to This Policy

We may update this Policy to reflect changes in features or legal requirements. Updates take effect upon posting within the app.

Contact

For privacy questions or requests, please contact support.
